# Task 10 – Create a Flow for Notification

## Project

**Virtual Agent–Driven SLA Breach Awareness & Justification System**

---

## Objective

This task automates SLA notifications using ServiceNow Flow Designer. When an Incident reaches 80% of its SLA duration, the flow updates the Incident record and sends email notifications to both the assignee and the manager.

---

## Navigation

**Process Automation → Flow Designer → New Flow**

---

## Flow Information

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Flow Name | SLA at Risk Notification |
| Application | Global |
| Trigger | Task SLA |
| Condition | Business Elapsed Percentage > 80% |

---

## Actions Configured

- Look Up Incident Record
- Update Incident Record
- Send Email to Assignee
- Send Email to Manager
- Activate Flow

---

## Deliverables

- Flow Configuration
- Trigger Configuration
- Email Notifications
- Incident Update Automation
- Flow Screenshots

---

## Expected Outcome

The Flow Designer automation detects SLA risk, updates the Incident record, and proactively notifies the assignee and manager, improving SLA governance and operational efficiency.

---

## Status

**Completed**

